            <title>[CASSANDRA-18764] CEP-15 (C*) When a host replacement happens don&apos;t loose the peer mapping right away</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18764</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a host replacement happens the latest epoch will no longer have the removed peer, but we may have in-flight messages that still reference it.  When C* restarts we need to also filter out these peers so we don&#8217;t wait for an epoch ack.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
